oc:kn_128823dd a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating an interview guide" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structure interview guides as: 1) Warm-up (5 min) — rapport + session intro. 2) Context (10 min) — current workflow understanding. 3) Deep dive (20 min) — core topic exploration. 4) Reaction (10 min) — concept/prototype feedback. 5) Wrap-up (5 min) — open questions + thanks." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This structure builds trust before probing deeply, ensures contextual understanding, and leaves room for participant-driven insights." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_92b304e1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting a research method" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Match research method to goal: interviews for deep needs (5-8 participants), usability tests for design evaluation (5-8), surveys for quantification (100+), card sorting for IA (15-30), diary studies for longitudinal behavior (10-15), A/B testing for design comparisons (statistical significance)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each method has different strengths, sample size requirements, and time commitments that determine validity of findings." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b7aa8848 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scoping qualitative research" ;
    oc:directiveContent "User interviews and usability testing require only 5-8 participants to reach thematic saturation; larger samples are not needed for qualitative methods." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Research shows that 5-8 participants uncover ~85% of usability issues. More participants yield diminishing returns for qualitative methods." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d3a00466 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When synthesizing research data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use four analysis frameworks: affinity mapping (group observations into themes), impact/effort matrix (prioritize findings), journey mapping (visualize experience over time), and jobs-to-be-done (understand product hiring intent)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multiple analysis lenses ensure findings are triangulated and actionable rather than biased toward a single interpretation." .

oc:kn_d77ceb8d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When completing a user research study" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Expected deliverables: 1) Research plan (objectives, methods, timeline, participants). 2) Interview guide (questions, probes, activities). 3) Synthesis report (themes, insights, recommendations). 4) Highlight reel (key quotes and observations)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These four deliverables cover the full research lifecycle from planning through presentation of findings." .

